messages.content: What are easy-comfy-nodes and where are they located within ComfyUI installation?
easy-comfy-nodes are a set of utility nodes for ComfyUI that are stored under `ComfyUI/custom_nodes/easy-comfy-nodes`.
How do I restart ComfyUI after making changes to easy-comfy-nodes?
To restart ComfyUI after making changes to easy-comfy-nodes, simply restart the ComfyUI application.
What is the prefix used for easy-comfy-nodes?
The prefix used for easy-comfy-nodes is `EZ`.
What does the VideoCombine node do?
The VideoCombine node assembles an animated webp and uploads it to s3, returning the s3 url.
What is the purpose of the HTTP POST node?
The HTTP POST node emits a POST request to a specified `url` with a provided `body` as JSON.
What is the function of the Load Img From URL node?
The Load Img From URL node loads an image from a specified url.
How does the Load Img Batch From URLs node operate?
The Load Img Batch From URLs node loads a batch of images from a set of URLs provided on separate lines.
What does the Empty Dict node in easy-comfy-nodes return?
The Empty Dict node returns an empty dictionary.
What does the Assoc X node in easy-comfy-nodes do?
The Assoc X node associates a specific `key` with a `value` of type X within a dictionary.
